article.headline: Morgan St. 57, Delaware St. 54
article.story: NEWARK, Del. -- Reggie Holmes scored 11 of his 15 points in the second half and Morgan State defeated Delaware State 57-54 on Monday night. After leading 21-20 at halftime and shooting 28.6 percent from the field in the first (6 of 21), Morgan State (12-10, 7-2 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference) outscored Delaware State 46-43 in the second. Down 50-52 with 3:21 left, Morgan State tied the game at 52-all on a layup by Rogers Barnes with 3 minutes to play. The Bears then took the lead for good on a free throw by Reggie Holmes. The Hornets (5-18, 3-5) pulled within 55-54 with 57 seconds to go on a Frisco Sandidge dunk, but couldn't convert a Morgan State turnover into points in the final 26 seconds. Bolden hit two free throws in the final second to ice the game. Donald Johnson scored 15 points for Delaware State, while Marcus Neal and Sandidge added 13 apiece.
